(2162, 1, '2015-03-05 12:15:24', '2015-03-05 12:15:24', 'Starting a food market in the heart of the Old East of Pretoria has been a passion of ours for years and so it was with great excitement that we opened the Hazel Food Market on 24 January 2009.  Of course the market is only as good as its vendors and that’s where you come in.  Our vision was to create a European-style food market where people can come and buy fresh food products.  We have an area with tables and benches where people can sit down, relax and enjoy the products they’ve just bought.  Our objective is to provide a range of delicious fresh products at affordable prices.  We require each stall to have taste samples available for people to taste the products where possible.\n\nThe Hazel Food Market is open every Saturday from 8h00-14h00. You have to bring your own table and gazebo and the cost is R300 per Saturday for a stall. To apply to be a vendor at the Hazel Food Market please complete the form. You''ll also be asked to bring taste samples of your products to the market for approval. Once they''re approved you''ll go on to the waiting list for a stall and be invited to participate in special markets.', 'Testing Contact Page', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'testing-contact-page', '', '', '2015-03-05 12:15:24', '2015-03-05 12:15:24', '', 0, 'http://ava-themes.com/WP/TuscanyXML/?page_id=2162', 0, 'page', '', 0),
